  "monologue": "This user benefits from small, structured steps and predictable routines. Evening cues can trigger substitutions; a single, protein/fiber-balanced snack plus a brief post-meal check-in reduces impulsive choices and reinforces mindful eating, building momentum toward the higher target without overwhelming changes.",
  "utterance": "Great plan. Today, commit to one mindful option: a balanced snack with protein and fiber (examples: Greek yogurt with berries, or an apple with a tablespoon of peanut butter). After dinner, take 2 minutes to check in on your fullness and log a one-word note (like 'satisfied' or 'full'). If you feel a urge to snack, pause for 60 seconds and choose the mindful option you planned. Keep portions small and pre-portion if possible so the choice feels automatic. This small, steady step will help you edge toward healthier patterns without needing perfection.",
  "endkey": false
}
